JOHANNESBURG - The South African Reserve Bank (Sarb) says it will no longer accept offers to purchase its shares.This follows its offer of more than 149,000 shares to the public.READ: Reserve Bank shares go on saleResponse from potential investors has been overwhelming.Two-hundred shares will give shareholders one vote to elect non-executive directors at the central bank.Governor Lesetja Kganyago says the offer was an attempt to diversify shareholder representation.eNCA